  if(d <= 1) proba = proba + 1

proba
## [1] 0.4747475
  • Graficar la funcin de distribucin emprica de la variable Diff.
distrEmpirica = function(V){
  return = 1:length(V)
  for (i in 1:length(V)) {
    res = 0
    for (d in dif) {
      if(d <= V[i]) res = res + 1
    }
    return[i] = res / length(dif)
  }
  return(return)
}
x = seq(-41,50,0.5)
plot(x,distrEmpirica(x),,xlim = c(-41,50),type="l")

disEmp1 = function(V){
  return = 1:length(V)
  for (i in 1:length(V)) {
    res = 0
    for (d in ly_diag1) {
      if(d <= V[i]) res = res + 1
    }
    return[i] = res / length(ly_diag1)
  }
  return(return)
}
disEmp2 = function(V){

    }
    return[i] = res / length(ly_diag2)
  }
  return(return)
}
